SIMPLE: lunatic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lunatic
<hw>Lu"na*tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>lunatique</ets>, L. <ets>lunaticus</ets>, fr. <ets>luna</ets> the
moon. See <er>Lunar</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Affected by lunacy;
insane; mad; crazy; demented.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lord, have mercy on my son; for he is <qex>lunatic</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wyclif (Matt. xvii. 15).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to, or suitable for, an insane
person; evincing lunacy; <as>as, <ex>lunatic</ex> gibberish; a
<ex>lunatic</ex> asylum.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lunatic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lunatic
<hw>Lu"na*tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person affected by lunacy; an
insane person, esp. one who has lucid intervals; a madman; a person of
unsound mind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>lunatic</qex>, the lover, and the poet,⟦br⟧
Are of imagination all compact.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lunatic fringe</ent>⟦br⟧
